{
  "text": "Since combustion control is affected by fuel properties, using oxygenated fuels can help enable LLFC because oxygen in the fuel changes the equivalence ratio of the fuel-air mixture. [CITATION_1] Oxygenated fuels are chemical compounds containing oxygen, which can be contained in many types of functional groups (e.g. ether, carbonyl, alcohol, ester and carbonate).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "93769111"
